974
00:45:49,766 --> 00:45:50,486
I kept bugging them.


975
00:45:50,486 --> 00:45:51,526
And at the time I was working


976
00:45:51,526 --> 00:45:53,966
with a division called Custom
Publishing, where we would work


977
00:45:53,966 --> 00:45:56,736
with clients outside of
Marvel, whether it was Visa


978
00:45:56,736 --> 00:45:59,376
or Cirque du Soleil, or
Harley-Davidson, you name it.


979
00:45:59,816 --> 00:46:00,946
We would create things
like those --


980
00:46:00,996 --> 00:46:03,346
does anyone remember those
old Hostess fruit pie ads


981
00:46:03,346 --> 00:46:04,456
with our characters?


982
00:46:04,956 --> 00:46:07,086
Yeah! That was good stuff!


983
00:46:07,466 --> 00:46:08,576
That's the kind of
stuff we made.


984
00:46:08,576 --> 00:46:12,146
We would make comics
posters, advertisements,


985
00:46:12,146 --> 00:46:14,586
using our characters in an
authentically Marvel way,


986
00:46:15,016 --> 00:46:16,306
to also promote another brand.


987
00:46:16,366 --> 00:46:20,196
So, finally we partnered with
the Children's Hearing Institute


988
00:46:20,486 --> 00:46:22,526
and we made a comic book!


989
00:46:22,946 --> 00:46:25,686
But we decided, hey let's use
Iron Man front and center.


990
00:46:26,096 --> 00:46:28,426
Why? We want to get
everyone's attention.


991
00:46:29,016 --> 00:46:31,236
He's one of our most
famous characters now.


992
00:46:31,456 --> 00:46:33,906
But not only is he
famous, he's a metaphor.


993
00:46:34,436 --> 00:46:35,776
We used him as a metaphor.


994
00:46:36,666 --> 00:46:39,456
We said to the kids, hey, if
you have to wear a hearing aid


995
00:46:39,456 --> 00:46:41,936
like Blue Ear or if you have
to wear a cochlear implant,


996
00:46:42,686 --> 00:46:44,756
that's Saphira on the
other side, in the pink,


997
00:46:45,256 --> 00:46:47,126
because this is in the
tradition of Women of Power,


998
00:46:47,126 --> 00:46:48,866
we wanted to have
a female character


999
00:46:49,606 --> 00:46:50,756
for young women to see.


1000
00:46:51,226 --> 00:46:52,766
So, we said, hey, if you
have to wear a hearing aid


1001
00:46:52,766 --> 00:46:54,816
or cochlear implant,
you're just like Tony Stark.


1002
00:46:55,456 --> 00:46:57,926
He uses his tech to
be the best he can be.


1003
00:46:57,926 --> 00:47:00,706
You can use your tech to
be the best you can be.


1004
00:47:01,486 --> 00:47:04,876
And the comic came out, and the
day it came out I got emails


1005
00:47:04,876 --> 00:47:07,516
from Italy and Australia
saying, thank you and asking


1006
00:47:07,516 --> 00:47:09,496
for copies of the comic book.


1007
00:47:10,496 --> 00:47:13,366
And that created
another wave of press.


1008
00:47:13,366 --> 00:47:14,836
Yes, it did not stop.


1009
00:47:15,186 --> 00:47:20,556
And one day I get a call and
I was asked to go on CNN.


1010
00:47:21,676 --> 00:47:23,586
I'm like, alright.


1011
00:47:24,256 --> 00:47:29,566
So, I'm in the limo
going into Manhattan.


1012
00:47:29,616 --> 00:47:32,256
Mom. Yes Billy?


1013
00:47:32,986 --> 00:47:35,786
Mom, in half hour I
want you to turn on CNN.


1014
00:47:35,786 --> 00:47:38,096
I'm going to be on.


1015
00:47:38,096 --> 00:47:39,306
Billy, what did you do?


1016
00:47:40,646 --> 00:47:41,376
No, mom it's good!


1017
00:47:41,376 --> 00:47:41,856
It's Blue Ear.


1018
00:47:41,886 --> 00:47:42,336
It's Blue Ear.


1019
00:47:42,336 --> 00:47:43,936
He's going to be on the show.


1020
00:47:43,936 --> 00:47:45,956
And actually, Christina and
Anthony are going to be there


1021
00:47:45,956 --> 00:47:47,206
and we're going to meet up.


1022
00:47:48,026 --> 00:47:49,646
And they're all going
to be able to meet.


1023
00:47:49,706 --> 00:47:50,586
And then guess what.


1024
00:47:51,336 --> 00:47:52,966
Then we're going into the
Marvel office together.


1025
00:47:53,516 --> 00:48:04,626
[ Applause ]


1026
00:48:05,126 --> 00:48:07,076
So, there's Nelson, who
created the cover piece.


1027
00:48:07,526 --> 00:48:09,196
There's me, grinning
like an idiot.


1028
00:48:09,406 --> 00:48:11,716
And there's Anthony,
and you'll notice he's


1029
00:48:11,716 --> 00:48:13,046
in the whole Blue Ear costume,


1030
00:48:13,046 --> 00:48:16,466
because mom saw how
excited Anthony was.


1031
00:48:16,466 --> 00:48:18,276
And he felt like, I'm
going to be Blue Ear.


1032
00:48:19,076 --> 00:48:19,956
And so he dresses up like this


1033
00:48:19,956 --> 00:48:21,736
and now the town
knows him as Blue Ear.


1034
00:48:21,736 --> 00:48:23,876
And guess who was
the Grand Marshall


1035
00:48:23,876 --> 00:48:28,106
of his town's Halloween parade
last year; Anthony as Blue Ear.


1036
00:48:28,686 --> 00:48:33,866
So, these Marvel characters;
why do we make them?


1037
00:48:34,866 --> 00:48:36,086
Power and responsibility.


1038
00:48:37,146 --> 00:48:38,166
What can we learn from them?


1039
00:48:38,856 --> 00:48:41,256
We have to use our
powers responsibly.


1040
00:48:41,626 --> 00:48:44,246
Now, you may be thinking,
Bill I can't climb a wall.


1041
00:48:44,246 --> 00:48:45,906
I can't leap through the sky.


1042
00:48:45,906 --> 00:48:47,916
I don't have rays
coming out of my eyes.


1043
00:48:47,916 --> 00:48:52,916
No, but everyone in this
room is incredibly smart


1044
00:48:53,446 --> 00:48:55,536
and incredibly gifted
with the skills you need


1045
00:48:55,886 --> 00:48:57,556
to create good things.


1046
00:48:57,916 --> 00:49:01,786
We have to use and realize
what our powers are.


1047
00:49:02,156 --> 00:49:06,556
We need to use them to create
things, to reach out to people


1048
00:49:06,556 --> 00:49:10,006
like Anthony, and kids around
the world of all ages like that.


1049
00:49:10,336 --> 00:49:14,056
We must use our creations to
make the world a better place.


1050
00:49:14,216 --> 00:49:14,936
Thank you very much.


1051
00:49:15,516 --> 00:49:19,500
[ Applause ]

